The halibut was dry and lacked any flaky texture.
The lamb had no flavor whatsoever.
I even forgot what I had for dessert.
I will admit that the service was very good.
The waiters were attentive and stirred up good conversation with us.
The actual Picasso paintings were beautiful and i really enjoyed viewing them.
I come to Vegas a lot, so the Bellagio fountains don't really thrill me anymore.
However, I can see how most people would find this to be interesting for their dining experience.
If you have experienced at least a 1 Michelin star restaurant, Picasso will disappoint you.
I would avoid this restaurant at all costs and use your money for the tables instead.
