Tourist trap?
Maybe, maybe not.
I always feel like a tourist when I go on the strip, despite being a local.
Coming to Picasso's makes me want to stay in the restaurant forever and never leave.
Combining food with art is such a brilliant idea- why didn't I think of this myself?!
I would tell you what we ate but I have this strange feeling that the menu will completely change once you get there (another completely brilliant business plan).
The most important points to take note of are the following:  1) Make a reservation- weeks in advance if you want to come during a holiday.
2) Make sure you're not nearing your credit limit.
This place will do no favors to your wallet.
3)  The portions are 'made to taste'.
If you want a truly hearty meal, go to the in-and-out across the street.
4) Business casual!!!
Girl with the cutoff jeans- not cool!
5) Spare a couple of minutes to take in the art.
It's not everyday you get to eat with works of Picasso all around you!

