OHHH MYYY...
I will be dreaming about this dining experience for days...   My boyfriend and I sat on the patio which is right on the fountain.
Beautiful view day or night.
We happened to be there for dinner.
The waiter was friendly, funny, and provided good conversation.
The fountain goes off every 30 minutes and there is a different show each time.
Very romantic setting with the fountain, music and the restaurant atmosphere.
Do bring a jacket if you are coming in the evening, it got pretty cold since it was windy.
Now for the good part.
They had a set menu with either a 5 course meal for $125 or a 4 course meal for $115.
They also had a wine pairing with the 5 course meal for additional cost but we didn't do that.
For new guests, they gave us a complimentary appetizer of potato soup with a coquette.
First course is the lobster salad.
It tastes really fresh and rejuvenating, I've never had that feeling from eating anything.
Second was a seared scallop with mashed potato.
The scallop was amazing.
It was perfectly crispy on the outside and soft inside.
The crunchiness of the chip and the soft scallop and potato made an interesting texture combo too.
Third was the foie gras.
I did not know it was a duck organ.
We were looking at the ducks that were begging for food and our waiter comes over and asks which foie gras I would like to have.
I've never had foie gras before, but it was the first time food literally melted in my mouth.
I did not know it was liver until later.
I did feel bad that the duck is force fed until they get fat, but it was so delicious.
For the fourth dish, I selected the roasted lamb while my boyfriend chose the halibut with asparagus.
I should have gotten the lamb more rare, I chose medium, so it was a bit tough.
The halibut was really good as well.
While waiting for dessert, they brought out a small dessert pastry tray.
I was already really full and we were running late for a show, so we unfortunately didn't finish the dessert.
My boyfriend had the earl grey cheesecake with blackberry, really great.
Sweet but not too sweet.
I had the warm chocolate fondant which has banana brulee and banana caramel ice cream.
The chocolate fondant was really good and the chocolate was made on the spot, but it was too sweet for my taste even though I really enjoyed it.
Overall, best restaurant experience I've ever had.
They excelled in every possible way.
Definitely can see why it has 2 Michelin Stars.
I wish I could try every single item on their menu.
While writing this review I looked through their menu for the dish names and now I'm just craving...Guess I need to plan another trip to Vegas soon!

I have had many experiences in my life, but Jose Serrano's food at Picasso was one of the truly memorable nights I had in my life.
I was there with my partner and celebrating 7 years of being together made it all more special at this place.
The service from beggining to end was spotless.
The ambience is perfect, the real Picassos around you set the scene.
You are in a museum, you are in a restaurant, food is art.
Which brings us to José Serrano's Truffle Menu with Wine Pairing.
It is really hard to describe all the flavours i discovered that night.
Each bite was exquisite, from the Egg Pollé, through the risotto, ravioli butternut squash and filet mignon, the truffles are always present.
If you live to go somewhere do not miss Picasso one of my most exhilarating gastronomical experiences.

One of the best meals I've ever had in my life!
This place truly provides a unique culinary experience, while also serving as a small museum displaying multi million dollar Picasso originals.
The decor is elegant and expensive feeling, and the restaurant is located right in front of the bellagio water fountain show (you really can't get a better view).
We did the pre fix menu, a 5 course delight!
The staff was extremely professional and explained every detail of each dish.
Each and every course came out as the chefs work of art...I really didn't want to eat it it was so beautiful!
The highlight of the night was my choice of deer medallions with caramelized apples and beans with a wine reduction.
With the fabulous glass of wine it was paired with, out of this world!!
Really a luxurious experience you won't get anywhere else.
If you have the funds to splurge, DO IT!
Highly recommended!

My first Michelin-starred restaurant experience, and it did not disappoint!
Picasso is tucked inside the Bellagio Hotel.
The entrance to the restaurant will require you to take a flight of stairs down, making it seemingly exclusive - and rightfully so.
It's a great spot to celebrate a special occasion or if you just have that much money lying around for a casual dinner.
The food, service, and atmosphere here is commendable.
Aside from the carefully-selected dishes offered, you have the opportunity to dine in a room full of original Picasso paintings.
It's amore!

